<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="348" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d348">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">President <persName corresp="#p_WW1">Wilson</persName>’s Files</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the
                                    Special Representative</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HEM1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">House</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-30">
                                        <hi rend="italic">October 30, 1918</hi>
                                    </date><note n="1" xml:id="d348fn1">Hour of dispatch not
                                        recorded.</note>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Analysis of fourteen points<note n="2" xml:id="d348fn2">Reference is
                                    to the Special Representative’s telegram No. 5 of Oct. 29, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_405">p.
                                    405</ref>.</note> satisfactory interpretation of principles
                                involved but details of application mentioned should be regarded as
                                merely illustrative suggestions and reserved for peace conference.
                                Admission of inchoate nationalities to peace conference most
                                undesirable.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_WW1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>